    "analysis": "We ran metric analysis (global P95 per (cmdb_id, kpi_name)) and found two prominent anomaly groups during 2022-03-21 13:30–14:00 (UTC+8): (1) adservice/adservice2 showing sustained process/Thread/GC/heap spikes and (2) currencyservice pods showing large container memory RSS increases. Trace analysis (global P95 per (cmdb_id, trace_name)) indicated elevated request volumes centered on frontend pods and increased calls from frontend to productcatalogservice, plus a strong latency spike between frontend and cartservice around ~13:52. The metric anomalies (adservice, currencyservice) do not obviously appear as downstream in the top trace anomalies (which are frontend → productcatalogservice and frontend → cartservice). To decide which faulty component actually caused the single failure, we need log evidence (error spikes, warnings, or operational messages) and to check trace error_rates to see which services experienced failures (not just traffic spikes). Therefore the next step is a compact log anomaly scan across components and log types to detect error_count or other log spikes in the incident window, using global thresholds computed from full series.",
